<title>BELGIUM: Belgian Renault workers refuse to see Schweitzer.</title>
<headline>Belgian Renault workers refuse to see Schweitzer.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-03-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Unions at the Belgian assembly plant of French car maker Renault said they turned down a proposal by Renault chief Louis Schweitzer for him to attend a works council meeting in Belgium on Thursday.</p>
<p>A spokesman said some 300 Belgian union representatives would now travel to Paris on Thursday morning for consultations before a meeting between Schweitzer and French unions.</p>
<p>Outraged by Renault's decision to close its plant in Vilvoorde near Brussels without consultation, unions have said they only want to talk to Schweitzer about a re-opening of the plant which employs 3,100, not about a social plan.</p>
